Deploy WAR File to Tomcat (Manual Deployment)
🎯 Objective

After Maven build:

Copy .war file to Tomcat webapps directory
Deploy application
🧱 Prerequisites
Maven build working
Tomcat installed:
/home/oracle/tools/apache-tomcat-9.0.115
Jenkins has permission to write to webapps
🔐 Fix Permissions (Important)
sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /home/oracle/tools/apache-tomcat-9.0.115/webapps
🔧 Jenkins Build Script
export MAVEN_HOME=/home/oracle/tools/maven/apache-maven-3.9.12
export PATH=$MAVEN_HOME/bin:$PATH

cd GRRAS

echo "Building project..."
mvn clean install

echo "Removing old deployment..."
rm -rf /home/oracle/tools/apache-tomcat-9.0.115/webapps/GRRAS*

echo "Copying WAR file..."
cp target/*.war /home/oracle/tools/apache-tomcat-9.0.115/webapps/

echo "Deployment Done ✅"
